05:16.316 --> 05:18.660
You're late. Now I'm
going to be late.

05:18.693 --> 05:20.661
<i>Nice to see you, too.</i>

05:20.695 --> 05:23.824
Someone has been crying his
little head off all morning.

05:23.907 --> 05:25.500
The bloody
washing machine's broken.

05:25.575 --> 05:27.669
I'm having to wash
everything in the sink.

05:27.744 --> 05:30.748
<i>Speaking of which... Don't
push your luck, Mommy.</i>

05:30.831 --> 05:35.428
Godmothers babysit, we buy
presents, we don't do laundry.

05:35.502 --> 05:37.675
Someone's very grumpy.

05:37.712 --> 05:39.589
You got your period?
No.

05:39.673 --> 05:42.722
It's sushi night,
actually.

05:42.801 --> 05:45.099
<i>You're not still doing
that, are you? Yeah.</i>

05:45.178 --> 05:47.055
You might as well wear
a T-shirt saying,

05:47.138 --> 05:49.607
"Hi, I'm ovulating.
Do you want to fuck?"

05:49.683 --> 05:54.063
<i>What's the romance in that'? Darling,
you do know, if! had the money, I'd...</i>

05:54.145 --> 05:56.614
Well, actually, I'd first go
buy a new washing machine,

05:56.690 --> 06:00.035
but then after that I'd pay
for you to go private.

06:00.068 --> 06:02.241
<i>I'd IVF you a baby.</i>

06:05.365 --> 06:07.459
How's Tom?

06:07.534 --> 06:10.128
He's just spending every
waking minute at the house.

06:11.580 --> 06:13.628
You're so lucky
to have him.

06:13.707 --> 06:16.802
And you're so lucky
to have him.

06:19.337 --> 06:21.590
<i>Tom. Tom.</i>

06:22.883 --> 06:24.351
You up there?

06:28.221 --> 06:30.098
What you doing?
Didn't you hear me?

06:32.183 --> 06:33.981
Job I just finished
had a little extra.

06:34.060 --> 06:35.937
<i>Thought you
could use them.</i>

06:38.565 --> 06:40.442
You all right, mate?

06:40.525 --> 06:43.153
I think we're going to lose the house.
<i>Oh, shit.</i>

06:43.236 --> 06:46.331
I thought you were coming along.
<i>Yeah.</i>

06:46.406 --> 06:49.501
Not far enough.

06:49.576 --> 06:52.455
Pumped all
the money into it.

06:52.537 --> 06:56.087
Half my budget went into
this fucking dry rot.

06:59.127 --> 07:01.676
What does Anna say?

07:01.755 --> 07:03.928
I haven't told her, yet.

07:03.965 --> 07:08.015
She only knows half of what I spent
and she's already freaking out.

07:08.094 --> 07:11.519
We're trying to start a family. Can't
even afford the rent on our apartment.

07:11.598 --> 07:14.522
Just talk to her, mate.
She'll understand.

07:16.394 --> 07:18.613
Come on.

07:21.983 --> 07:24.863
If you're up for it, a friend of mine
needs some painting done next week.

07:24.903 --> 07:27.156
Won't pay much, but...

07:27.238 --> 07:31.209
Yeah.
Thanks.

07:31.284 --> 07:35.209
It's a good thing I have a Master's degree.
Come in handy.

07:35.288 --> 07:36.790
See you, bud.

07:49.135 --> 07:51.809
Tom Wright?
Yeah.

07:54.808 --> 07:56.651
You're served.

07:59.771 --> 08:02.115
We've got two weeks?

08:04.401 --> 08:06.028
Thanks.

08:18.665 --> 08:20.759
Ben.

08:20.834 --> 08:23.053
Turn it down.

08:37.017 --> 08:38.394
<i>Hello?</i>

08:42.938 --> 08:46.193
Hi.

08:50.321 --> 08:52.574
It's, uh, sushi night?

08:52.657 --> 08:54.455
<i>You forgot.</i>

08:54.534 --> 08:56.753
No. No.

08:56.828 --> 09:00.378
I never forget sushi night.
It's fine.

09:00.457 --> 09:02.880
Nice wine.

09:02.959 --> 09:05.633
<i>It was just
a few quid extra.</i>

09:05.712 --> 09:08.886
A very nice wine. <i>And I
thought it was worth it.</i>

09:11.718 --> 09:13.971
Of course
it's worth it.

09:16.264 --> 09:18.733
Come here.

09:18.767 --> 09:20.360
Sushi night.

09:23.229 --> 09:24.321
How's Julian?

09:24.397 --> 09:28.402
He's... loud and...

09:29.986 --> 09:31.579
Tonight,
Yeah?

09:31.613 --> 09:33.615
Someone's going
to get pregnant.

10:03.895 --> 10:05.943
Hey.

10:07.941 --> 10:09.909
You Okay?

10:13.780 --> 10:16.624
We're going to lose
the house.

10:22.247 --> 10:23.794
No.

10:25.708 --> 10:28.962
No. We're going to work it out.

10:31.047 --> 10:33.891
<i>Mike just got me
a few days on a good job.</i>

10:35.927 --> 10:39.431
Maybe it's time we go back. No.

10:40.807 --> 10:42.650
No.
Tom.

10:42.725 --> 10:44.773
This was my idea.

10:47.814 --> 10:49.816
I promised you
a fresh start.

10:49.899 --> 10:53.824
I promised you a place
to start a family.

10:55.405 --> 10:57.578
That was then.

11:00.493 --> 11:02.416
I'm not giving up.

11:02.495 --> 11:05.999
So... you can shut up.

11:06.040 --> 11:08.839
Tonight is sushi night.

11:10.253 --> 11:11.505
I'm feeling lucky.

11:19.345 --> 11:20.767
<i>Ben.</i>

11:33.735 --> 11:35.362
Ben.

11:51.878 --> 11:53.095
No answer.

11:56.507 --> 11:58.305
Tom.

12:02.805 --> 12:04.557
Ben?

12:08.102 --> 12:09.854
I'm coming down.

12:18.029 --> 12:19.827
Ben.

12:29.582 --> 12:31.255
Ben?

12:31.334 --> 12:33.052
<i>Oh, Tom.</i>

12:43.096 --> 12:44.564
Oh, my God.

13:22.969 --> 13:25.222
I can't believe he was
down here the whole time.

13:25.305 --> 13:28.479
<i>Yeah. Right below
where our bedroom is.</i>

13:52.999 --> 13:55.377
Anna.
What?

14:17.815 --> 14:20.034
<i>Oh, my God, Tom.</i>

14:20.109 --> 14:23.113
220,000 pounds.

14:23.196 --> 14:25.949
What the hell was Ben doing
with this much cash?

14:26.032 --> 14:29.536
What was he doing living in our
basement with all this cash?

14:30.912 --> 14:34.587
Well, he was
on disability,

14:34.665 --> 14:38.420
and maybe he had a big
settlement after an accident?

14:38.503 --> 14:42.474
I just don't know why it
wouldn't be in the bank.

15:08.699 --> 15:10.042
So, what do we do?

15:13.162 --> 15:15.164
Hm?

15:17.083 --> 15:20.007
We call the police.
Yeah?

15:30.930 --> 15:32.773
Anna. Anna.
What?

15:32.849 --> 15:34.943
<i>Wait.</i>

15:35.017 --> 15:36.485
Tom.

15:38.438 --> 15:41.442
Help me. We shouldn't have
brought this up here.

15:41.524 --> 15:43.276
I know.
You want to help me?

15:43.359 --> 15:44.702
Tom.
Help me now.

15:48.281 --> 15:50.625
I got it.
Answer the door.

15:56.747 --> 15:58.624
Mr. Wright?
Yes.

15:58.666 --> 16:02.341
I'm Detective Inspector
John Haiden.

16:05.089 --> 16:08.184
So, Mr. Wright,
what-what is it you do?

16:08.259 --> 16:11.684
<i>He's a landscape architect.
Oh.</i>

16:11.762 --> 16:15.983
Yeah. I used to be, in Chicago.

16:16.058 --> 16:19.312
I had a small business,
a little crew,

16:19.395 --> 16:21.318
but it fell apart
in the crash,

16:21.397 --> 16:24.742
so we moved here
for a fresh start.

16:24.817 --> 16:29.414
We also had an unfortunate
miscarriage a few years ago, so...

16:29.489 --> 16:31.662
Oh, I'm so sorry.
So sorry.

16:31.699 --> 16:34.043
<i>It was a nice
change for us.</i>

16:34.118 --> 16:37.167
<i>So, now I-I do
contracting work</i>

16:37.246 --> 16:39.920
odd jobs
and manual labor.

16:39.999 --> 16:42.252
<i>Why London? Tom's
renovating</i> a <i>house.</i>

16:42.335 --> 16:45.430
<i>My grandmother
passed a few years ago</i>

16:45.505 --> 16:50.102
and we inherited the family house,
so I thought I'd fix it up.

16:50.176 --> 16:53.931
Good for you.

16:54.013 --> 16:57.438
So, Mrs. Wright, how are you,
um, how are you liking London?

16:57.517 --> 16:59.394
Anna, please.

16:59.477 --> 17:03.198
I'm a school teacher at
Morningside Primary school

17:03.272 --> 17:05.866
My wife runs a clinic just
down the street from there.

17:05.942 --> 17:09.913
<i>Sterling House? That's a,
uh, women's shelter, right?</i>

17:09.987 --> 17:13.958
<i>Yeah. They look after young women with
drug addiction, take them off the streets.</i>

17:14.032 --> 17:16.957
<i>The government has withdrawn its
funding, but they're hanging in there.</i>

17:17.036 --> 17:20.131
My wife, Marie,
isn't one for giving up.

17:25.836 --> 17:27.463
Anyhow...

17:27.547 --> 17:29.720
So, thank you
for the tea.

17:32.385 --> 17:34.228
<i>It was very good.</i>

17:36.305 --> 17:38.808
How long have you been
renting the room downstairs?

17:38.891 --> 17:41.314
Uh, not long.

17:41.394 --> 17:45.444
I mean, we just did it 'cause
we needed help with the rent.

17:45.523 --> 17:47.400
Three months, maybe.
<i>Yeah.</i>

17:47.483 --> 17:51.829
And he always paid by cash.
Did you find this odd?

17:53.406 --> 17:55.579
No, not really, no.

17:55.658 --> 17:57.581
Did he, um,

17:57.618 --> 18:00.121
did he have
any visitors?

18:03.207 --> 18:08.964
Uh, he really kept to himself.
I mean, he didn't have much.

18:09.046 --> 18:11.424
No. He watched a
lot of television.

18:11.507 --> 18:14.260
<i>Yeah, that's true.
Very loud.</i>

18:14.302 --> 18:18.307
Did, um, did you find
anything unusual about him?

18:23.853 --> 18:26.106
When you, um,

18:26.188 --> 18:29.192
when you discovered
he body, did you...

18:29.275 --> 18:31.403
Did you find
anything else?

18:34.739 --> 18:37.288
Um...
No.

18:37.325 --> 18:40.499
The reason I ask is because
the initial police report

18:40.578 --> 18:43.297
suggests that he died
of a drug overdose,

18:43.372 --> 18:45.670
and the team downstairs are
just looking for evidence

18:45.750 --> 18:47.878
that he may
have kept drugs there.

18:47.960 --> 18:51.464
No, we had... I mean,
we had no idea.

18:53.924 --> 18:57.474
Well, it's just, uh...
it's just routine.

18:57.553 --> 18:59.351
For your own safety.

19:16.489 --> 19:18.366
<i>...late 40's</i>

19:18.449 --> 19:20.827
<i>discovered in the basement
of a flat.</i>

19:20.868 --> 19:23.212
<i>The cause of death
is as yet unknown.</i>

19:23.287 --> 19:26.712
<i>His identity is being withheld
until relatives are traced.</i>

19:26.791 --> 19:29.795
<i>To the city now, and London's
markets are still not steady.</i>

19:37.301 --> 19:39.099
<i>There's a new lead</i>

19:39.178 --> 19:42.557
to-to the guys that
gave Julie the drugs.

19:44.183 --> 19:46.527
I thought Martin
took you off that case.

19:46.602 --> 19:48.195
<i>Yeah.</i>

19:50.940 --> 19:53.068
Is it dangerous?

19:55.695 --> 19:58.164
<i>Really dangerous, then.</i>

20:00.199 --> 20:02.418
<i>Still not going
to bring her back, John.</i>

20:02.493 --> 20:05.042
So,

20:05.079 --> 20:06.581
why take the risk?

20:09.917 --> 20:12.386
It might save
someone else's daughter.

20:17.216 --> 20:19.765
We'll call Haiden
in the morning.

21:04.013 --> 21:06.015
Tom?

21:08.100 --> 21:10.023
Tom?

21:34.752 --> 21:36.846
What are you doing?

21:47.097 --> 21:49.896
<i>We spent our whole lives
being good, right?</i>

21:49.975 --> 21:54.731
And what has it gotten us?
Nothing.

21:54.814 --> 21:59.160
<i>So, maybe this money is a gift to
help us get our lives back on track.</i>

21:59.235 --> 22:01.158
Tom.

22:03.113 --> 22:05.491
We don't know where
this money comes from.

22:07.743 --> 22:12.374
This could be really,
really bad money.

22:16.836 --> 22:20.010
But what makes
money bad?

22:20.089 --> 22:23.684
Not the money.
The people make it bad.

22:23.759 --> 22:26.012
What people do with it.

22:26.095 --> 22:29.395
Now, I'm not saying
we do anything rash.

22:31.892 --> 22:34.065
All I'm saying is we
just wait and see.

22:34.144 --> 22:37.114
He's been dead a week.

22:37.189 --> 22:40.284
The cops came,
they didn't find anything.

22:40.359 --> 22:42.953
No one's come forward
looking for the money.

22:43.028 --> 22:45.406
Okay?
And if they do,

22:46.949 --> 22:49.247
this will look like
Ben hid it.

22:51.662 --> 22:54.290
I say
we just hide it

22:54.373 --> 22:57.217
and wait a week.

23:09.722 --> 23:11.144
Two weeks.

23:13.058 --> 23:14.685
All right.

23:17.396 --> 23:21.492
End of the month.
And then

23:23.068 --> 23:24.741
nobody comes,

23:27.197 --> 23:28.870
we just find it again.

23:44.256 --> 23:47.260
Haiden, where are the background
checks on the Scott case?

23:49.678 --> 23:53.933
You wouldn't be wasting time on the
Witkowski case? I told you to drop it.

23:53.974 --> 23:57.274
<i>Nobody gives a shit if Jack Witkowski
killed his twat of a brother.</i>

23:57.311 --> 24:01.282
<i>Another deficient shitsack off the
street is fine with this department.</i>

24:01.357 --> 24:05.032
The Scott background checks,
on my desk by five.

24:20.960 --> 24:24.965
And this has nothing
to do with Julie?

24:25.005 --> 24:27.178
No, no, no, no.
It's just...

24:27.257 --> 24:29.976
It's just a hunch
I want to follow up on.

24:32.638 --> 24:35.642
If I'm going to break every
law I'm here to uphold,

24:35.683 --> 24:37.401
I'd rather it was
for a good cause.

24:40.437 --> 24:42.110
Okay.

24:44.233 --> 24:47.157
It has everything
to do with my daughter.

24:51.865 --> 24:55.540
Bank accounts, Inland Revenue,
utility bills, mortgage.

24:55.619 --> 25:00.216
From now on, if Thomas or Anna
Wright sneeze, you'll know about it.

25:02.668 --> 25:05.342
But I warn you, there's
not much money to follow.

25:05.379 --> 25:07.677
No, not at the moment.

25:09.341 --> 25:11.093
Okay.

25:11.176 --> 25:14.271
You'll keep me posted?

25:14.346 --> 25:16.565
If Martin finds out,
I'll be fired.

25:16.640 --> 25:19.689
<i>Martin's a smug
little prick.</i>

25:19.768 --> 25:23.363
Superintendent Tosspot
can go fuck himself.

25:42.541 --> 25:44.543
<i>Detective Halden? Yes.</i>

25:44.626 --> 25:47.220
<i>Hi, this is
Tom Wright from</i> the...

25:47.254 --> 25:50.098
<i>How are you?
We were just wondering</i>

25:50.174 --> 25:54.645
<i>if you heard anything about the
next of kin for Ben Tuttle.</i>

25:54.720 --> 25:57.473
<i>No, no, no. We haven't located
any living relatives.</i>

25:58.766 --> 26:00.939
I just ask
because, uh,

26:01.018 --> 26:05.148
we wanted to know what do with his
things, his clothes and stuff.

26:05.230 --> 26:06.982
<i>No, no one's come
forward, yet.</i>

26:09.568 --> 26:11.320
Okay.

26:11.403 --> 26:15.158
And, uh, do you know,
was it officially...

26:15.240 --> 26:17.163
Yeah, overdose.

26:17.242 --> 26:19.336
Looks like
it was Liquid O.

26:19.411 --> 26:22.005
<i>What's Liquid O?
Heroin.</i>

26:22.081 --> 26:25.255
<i>I see.
Wow.</i>

26:25.334 --> 26:27.928
<i>Okay. Have a good day.</i> Bye.

27:15.008 --> 27:17.807
<i>You met my little
brother, haven't you?</i>

27:17.886 --> 27:20.810
Always tried
to let him win.

27:20.889 --> 27:23.517
Any game.

27:23.600 --> 27:25.523
Drove Mom crazy.

27:25.602 --> 27:27.821
Said Bobby would never
learn if we did that.

27:29.773 --> 27:32.196
'Course she was right.

27:34.027 --> 27:37.156
<i>Jack and Bobby.
How it came to this?</i>

27:37.197 --> 27:40.246
Mom was a fan.

27:40.325 --> 27:43.329
<i>She also had
high expectations.</i>

27:47.916 --> 27:49.088
Where's Cousin Ben?

27:54.381 --> 27:58.011
You know, when you
recommend a guy,

27:58.093 --> 28:01.438
<i>you're tying
his name to yours.</i>

28:01.513 --> 28:04.312
Did you know he was
going to fuck me?

28:06.185 --> 28:08.688
If you tell me
where I find him,

28:10.355 --> 28:12.733
maybe I'll choose
to believe you on that.

28:16.862 --> 28:19.786
Eddie, sir, could I please
trouble you for a pen?

28:38.467 --> 28:39.969
You done
the right thing.

28:42.888 --> 28:45.812
<i>But that doesn't mean I'm not
going to hold you accountable.</i>

29:31.603 --> 29:33.776
Anna.
Yeah.

29:35.732 --> 29:37.234
I spent some
of the money.

29:43.031 --> 29:44.453
What?

29:44.491 --> 29:46.960
<i>The day we found Ben,</i>

29:46.994 --> 29:50.715
<i>the landlord gave us
an eviction notice.</i>

29:50.789 --> 29:53.463
<i>I was going to tell you, but
you were in such a good mood,</i>

29:53.500 --> 29:56.470
<i>and it was sushi night.</i>

29:56.545 --> 29:59.219
And then we found
the money, and...

29:59.298 --> 30:02.177
I took just enough to keep
the roof over our heads.

30:04.219 --> 30:08.349
Look, we're in this.

30:08.432 --> 30:11.902
<i>As soon as we put the money in the oven and
we didn't take it out, we were in this.</i>

30:14.563 --> 30:17.737
If we don't start paying off the
mortgage, we're going to lose the house.

30:22.821 --> 30:24.414
How do we do this?

30:24.489 --> 30:27.163
We spend just enough
to stop the bleeding.

30:27.200 --> 30:29.578
We use cash
where we can,

30:29.661 --> 30:32.380
and we get Mike
to write an invoice.

30:32.456 --> 30:34.504
You want to bring Mike
into this?

30:34.583 --> 30:37.757
No, it's not like that. We're
not bringing him into it.

30:37.836 --> 30:41.716
But when I do a job for him,
he usually pays me cash,

30:41.798 --> 30:43.550
and then writes
an invoice.

30:43.633 --> 30:46.261
So, if anyone asks...

30:46.345 --> 30:49.394
<i>Right, there's
a paper trail.</i>

30:49.473 --> 30:52.477
What if someone comes
looking for it, Tom?

30:56.355 --> 30:58.028
Anna.

30:59.608 --> 31:02.361
Nobody's come.

31:02.402 --> 31:04.450
Nobody's going
to come.

31:04.529 --> 31:06.623
And if they do,

31:06.698 --> 31:09.247
who's to say
Ben didn't spend it?

31:09.326 --> 31:12.580
How much
are we talking?

31:12.662 --> 31:15.131
Just enough
to stay above water.

31:15.207 --> 31:17.756
The mortgage,
credit cards.

31:17.834 --> 31:20.303
